National Health Insurance (NHI) has become an idealistic concept known as “imaginary”. It’s become the idea on to which all South Africa’s aspirations for healthcare have been projected, the dream of a system that is fairer, less divided and more efficient. It’s even been called “pie in the sky”. It’s clear that some version of the NHI is going to happen regardless. And its success or failure will be determined by the extent to which all South Africans contribute to it. This dream of a single national health system could be realised if South Africa is able to articulate a...